<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7093&amp;p=69087#p69087"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[NROM game in a TLROM board]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7093&amp;p=69087#p69087"><![CDATA[
When the power is turned on, <strong>nobody knows</strong> what is in $8000-$DFFF until your code writes to those registers. There is no defined initial bank number. Your code still has to work even if random numbers are loaded into the bank registers at power on.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Mon Oct 25, 2010 11:22 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
